Was it easy to keep in touch with friends and family back home?

00:45:26.040 --> 00:45:27.040
Yes and no.

00:45:29.040 --> 00:45:34.040
Because not many people have a telephone.

00:45:34.040 --> 00:45:39.040
Only the wealthy do have telephones.

00:45:42.040 --> 00:45:50.040
You'd have to go to the town and then you could use a phone in the town.

00:45:53.040 --> 00:45:59.040
If I want to talk to my mom, I'd write her and give her a number.

00:45:59.040 --> 00:46:02.040
She can phone me at that special time.

00:46:02.040 --> 00:46:05.040
And then she could phone and then I'll be there.

00:46:06.040 --> 00:46:10.040
And then whoever owns the phone will talk to her and then hand it to me.

00:46:11.040 --> 00:46:15.040
And then you probably say, oh well, you have to pay such and such for the car.

00:46:16.040 --> 00:46:17.040
So I just do.

00:46:18.040 --> 00:46:23.040
Mom has to pay over here, but it's still cost a bit over there, so you have to pay for it.

00:46:23.040 --> 00:46:25.040
But you could still talk to people.

00:46:26.040 --> 00:46:28.040
When you're back home and talking.

00:46:29.040 --> 00:46:31.040
But mostly you're talking, you do two letters.

00:46:33.040 --> 00:46:36.040
You write a letter and send it through the post and she'll get it.

00:46:37.040 --> 00:46:40.040
That's how she used to send me money, through the post.

00:46:41.040 --> 00:46:45.040
And do you keep in touch with people in Jamaica now?

00:46:46.040 --> 00:46:47.040
Yeah, I do.

00:46:48.040 --> 00:46:49.040
I do.

00:46:49.040 --> 00:46:53.040
Not as often as I should do, but I still keep in touch with them.

00:46:54.040 --> 00:46:56.040
Now and again, I found them over there.

00:46:57.040 --> 00:46:59.040
And if anything goes wrong, they'll phone me.

00:47:01.040 --> 00:47:03.040
I try and help them if I can.

