Well, the music, when I came to the UK, I was playing music, my friend.

00:49:17.040 --> 00:49:18.040
That's not music.

00:49:21.040 --> 00:49:25.040
I said that's only one beat. The beat goes ching ching ching ching ching ching.

00:49:27.040 --> 00:49:32.040
I remember when I was going to school, in secondary, having a party.

00:49:32.040 --> 00:49:34.040
I said, bring your records in.

00:49:35.040 --> 00:49:40.040
I bring a few records in, and a few types, and I'm playing it.

00:49:42.040 --> 00:49:44.040
I said, where you get these records from?

00:49:45.040 --> 00:49:47.040
I said, those are my country music.

00:49:49.040 --> 00:49:50.040
Oh, they're good.

00:49:52.040 --> 00:49:54.040
Do you like our music? I said, not really.

00:49:56.040 --> 00:50:00.040
I said, your music is all chingy ling ling ling like a one string.

00:50:00.040 --> 00:50:02.040
I said, you have to put, you know what I mean?

00:50:03.040 --> 00:50:04.040
I said, there's no bass in it.

00:50:05.040 --> 00:50:12.040
I said, now you listen to this one, now you can hear the bass coming through, all the different instruments coming through.

00:50:13.040 --> 00:50:20.040
I said, yours is all chingy ling ling ling, every single one on the same, sound the same, especially the beakers.

00:50:21.040 --> 00:50:22.040
Which you know, killing yourself.

00:50:23.040 --> 00:50:28.040
I said, I'll tell you the other truth, I can't see the beauty about beakers.

00:50:28.040 --> 00:50:31.040
I said, to me, they're rubbish.

00:50:34.040 --> 00:50:37.040
They said, oh well, every man to his own culture.

00:50:38.040 --> 00:50:39.040
I said, well, there you are.

00:50:40.040 --> 00:50:42.040
I said, I couldn't put it better myself.

00:50:43.040 --> 00:50:44.040
Every man to his own culture.

